[tool-call] delta {"path":"tests/src/org.jboss.arquillian.config/arquillian-config-api/1.1.10.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_arquillian_config/arquillian_config_api/Arquillian_config_apiTest.java","edits":[{"oldText":"    @Test\n    void importedDescriptorCanBeModifiedAndReExported() {\n","newText":"    @Test\n    void descriptorPreservesMultilineAndXmlEscapedPropertyValuesAcrossExportAndImport() {\n        String startupScript = \"\"\"\n                if (serverName < target) {\n                    log(\"server & test\");\n                }\n                return \"ready\";\n                \"\"\".trim();\n        String protocolPayload = \"\"\"\n                {\n                  \"path\": \"/service?name=arquillian&mode=test\",\n                  \"enabled\": true\n                }\n                \"\"\".trim();\n        ArquillianDescriptor descriptor = newDescriptor(\"escaped-values.xml\");\n\n        descriptor.defaultProtocol(\"Servlet 3.0\")\n                .property(\"payload\", protocolPayload);\n        descriptor.container(\"scripted\")\n                .property(\"startupScript\", startupScript)\n                .protocol(\"HTTP\")\n                .property(\"requestPayload\", protocolPayload);\n        descriptor.extension(\"script-runner\")\n                .property(\"startupScript\", startupScript);\n\n        ArquillianDescriptor imported = Descriptors.importAs(ArquillianDescriptor.class, \"escaped-values.xml\")\n                .fromString(descriptor.exportAsString());\n\n        assertThat(imported.getDefaultProtocol().getProperties()).containsOnly(entry(\"payload\", protocolPayload));\n        ContainerDef scripted = onlyContainerNamed(imported.getContainers(), \"scripted\");\n        assertThat(scripted.getContainerProperties()).containsOnly(entry(\"startupScript\", startupScript));\n        assertThat(scripted.getProtocols().get(0).getProtocolProperties())\n                .containsOnly(entry(\"requestPayload\", protocolPayload));\n        assertThat(onlyExtensionNamed(imported.getExtensions(), \"script-runner\").getExtensionProperties())\n                .containsOnly(entry(\"startupScript\", startupScript));\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void importedDescriptorCanBeModifiedAndReExported() {\n"}]}
[tool-call] end id=call_xcbKqOzsPnaih6uSk3WrzZqE|fc_0aae0022768d63740169fda695e27881928fb854cbbedca87c name=edit args={"path": "tests/src/org.jboss.arquillian.config/arquillian-config-api/1.1.10.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_arquillian_config/arquillian_config_api/Arquillian_config_apiTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void importedDescriptorCanBeModifiedAndReExported() {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void descriptorPreservesMultilineAndXmlEscapedPropertyValuesAcrossExportAndImport() {\n        String startupScript = \"\"\"\n                if (serverName < target) {\n                    log(\"server & test\");\n                }\n                return \"ready\";\n                \"\"\".trim();\n        String protocolPayload = \"\"\"\n                {\n                  \"path\": \"/service?name=arquillian&mode=test\",\n                  \"enabled\": true\n                }\n                \"\"\".trim();\n        ArquillianDescriptor descriptor = newDescriptor(\"escaped-values.xml\");\n\n        descriptor.defaultProtocol(\"Servlet 3.0\")\n                .property(\"payload\", protocolPayload);\n        descriptor.container(\"scripted\")\n                .property(\"startupScript\", startupScript)\n                .protocol(\"HTTP\")\n                .property(\"requestPayload\", protocolPayload);\n        descriptor.extension(\"script-runner\")\n                .property(\"startupScript\", startupScript);\n\n        ArquillianDescriptor imported = Descriptors.importAs(ArquillianDescriptor.class, \"escaped-values.xml\")\n                .fromString(descriptor.exportAsString());\n\n        assertThat(imported.getDefaultProtocol().getProperties()).containsOnly(entry(\"payload\", protocolPayload));\n        ContainerDef scripted = onlyContainerNamed(imported.getContainers(), \"scripted\");\n        assertThat(scripted.getContainerProperties()).containsOnly(entry(\"startupScript\", startupScript));\n        assertThat(scripted.getProtocols().get(0).getProtocolProperties())\n                .containsOnly(entry(\"requestPayload\", protocolPayload));\n        assertThat(onlyExtensionNamed(imported.getExtensions(), \"script-runner\").getExtensionProperties())\n                .containsOnly(entry(\"startupScript\", startupScript));\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void importedDescriptorCanBeModifiedAndReExported() {\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating roundtrip assertions**\n\nI'm thinking about how to assert that a roundtrip equals, especially with strings like \"line one\\nline <two> & \\\"quoted\\\"\". It’s important that exporting escapes characters while importing preserves them. That seems really useful! But what if the export uses CDATA or escapes text differently? Maybe I shouldn't assert the exact escaping but rather that it's not broken and can handle a roundtrip well. I also wonder if special characters in attribute names need special handling.\n\n**Considering Java text blocks**\n\nI’m noticing that they prefer using Java multi-line strings with text blocks, which is interesting! But there could be a potential issue with text blocks, specifically when it comes to trailing newlines. I wonder if that could cause unexpected behavior in their code or if it's just a minor inconvenience. It's good to be aware of these details to avoid any problems in the future. Let's keep exploring this concept!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0aae0022768d63740169fda682f51c81928ebb88a1b4eaa610\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_aaVkLJbIJOz-ODgOvWI9pm8BtDHrN8wytTWfTdskFtwXP19tqDUKahzN34B3DWII6Zd8qHTSv22yhxmSUWdmlWvnTP5-nLwz4ustL2hr1kodLM5lFn55k5LLFQ7fQEqMuf08TMMPUQNaEgjjgE6f0Dl5D5Evu4K8D43aeYgEsv9x_KtcbDLekvk09goJ46Vns-g9f9Kw7xPWI4dbcTar95THG4torVTsFwfVgLyGdaPuytB0QJWlEEjw6S7ipg-MeEdIHmRKl9qxuiqbaqoatBGBgKHLFKw2sgQ5jDCvxF7xIIx3Ouf4155GvYWo1I5aDXwW39m23HopzViVX9lgkTYcTNdmxWuTrboyOTG1T1CW3JxApBJIGaYhqPUclfQQ9Q8Anwcnk9CIUc3wxVHPtwD1kgAENItWkpDtmbMYJon2B_LaMqamDMnl-sAUsslkK3dqRGOguw7ukFPtuqrwgEjRSplnPRPZPqmHhXJQYq6FELs09A6V1RZ7dLHynQas5uTuDsr2IuY4cImiee_HGDuoB11gv6hR2kQ23iT9OdzYU5xguIzeDpCUV2RL6pMyW83ewXB2fL-LGzYrUr-F7m9SY7uiXQcjzHP6O1Jjn2dxb9_VuZND22y0OLOLnKZ79tEq6pXkbtZMGsbm3yU8eq4TwOZGuHBulZSxoWDJhwNgw_Ovi09JbS0RqqtCX_r9Vco_UNWD6SvkfLxs9j_UwZ5aNbZCmPDzWm1iXFPF_0epBqjvNyPDd6rCK