[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating roundtrip assertions**\n\nI'm thinking about how to assert that a roundtrip equals, especially with strings like \"line one\\nline <two> & \\\"quoted\\\"\". It’s important that exporting escapes characters while importing preserves them. That seems really useful! But what if the export uses CDATA or escapes text differently? Maybe I shouldn't assert the exact escaping but rather that it's not broken and can handle a roundtrip well. I also wonder if special characters in attribute names need special handling.\n\n**Considering Java text blocks**\n\nI’m noticing that they prefer using Java multi-line strings with text blocks, which is interesting! But there could be a potential issue with text blocks, specifically when it comes to trailing newlines. I wonder if that could cause unexpected behavior in their code or if it's just a minor inconvenience. It's good to be aware of these details to avoid any problems in the future. Let's keep exploring this concept!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0aae0022768d63740169fda682f51c81928ebb88a1b4eaa610\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_aaVkLJbIJOz-ODgOvWI9pm8BtDHrN8wytTWfTdskFtwXP19tqDUKahzN34B3DWII6Zd8qHTSv22yhxmSUWdmlWvnTP5-nLwz4ustL2hr1kodLM5lFn55k5LLFQ7fQEqMuf08TMMPUQNaEgjjgE6f0Dl5D5Evu4K8D43aeYgEsv9x_KtcbDLekvk09goJ46Vns-g9f9Kw7xPWI4dbcTar95THG4torVTsFwfVgLyGdaPuytB0QJWlEEjw6S7ipg-MeEdIHmRKl9qxuiqbaqoatBGBgKHLFKw2sgQ5jDCvxF7xIIx3Ouf4155GvYWo1I5aDXwW39m23HopzViVX9lgkTYcTNdmxWuTrboyOTG1T1CW3JxApBJIGaYhqPUclfQQ9Q8Anwcnk9CIUc3wxVHPtwD1kgAENItWkpDtmbMYJon2B_LaMqamDMnl-sAUsslkK3dqRGOguw7ukFPtuqrwgEjRSplnPRPZPqmHhXJQYq6FELs09A6V1RZ7dLHynQas5uTuDsr2IuY4cImiee_HGDuoB11gv6hR2kQ23iT9OdzYU5xguIzeDpCUV2RL6pMyW83ewXB2fL-LGzYrUr-F7m9SY7uiXQcjzHP6O1Jjn2dxb9_VuZND22y0OLOLnKZ79tEq6pXkbtZMGsbm3yU8eq4TwOZGuHBulZSxoWDJhwNgw_Ovi09JbS0RqqtCX_r9Vco_UNWD6SvkfLxs9j_UwZ5aNbZCmPDzWm1iXFPF_0epBqjvNyPDd6rCK0Cx